The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Burdwan, March 6: A potato farmer in his mid-40s consumed pesticide today after having discovered that the crop on half of his five-acre plot had been destroyed. 

 Anil Bag was found dead on his field at Mangalkot, 180 km from Calcutta. Police said this is the third life claimed by blight, the disease that has wreaked havoc in potato plants this year. Bag had borrowed Rs 25,000 to purchase fertilisers and pesticides.

 Suri: Class XII student Suchitra Mal was found dead in a bush at Nalhati, 280 km from Calcutta, on Tuesday. Four men in their early 20s were held following a complaint lodged by her family.




